70. tre ( Wait its less than 6 letters)
 Remove it from the list

 There are 12 words left.

 Long word percentage (L) = (12/70 * 100% ≈ 17.14%

3. Calculate LIX.  LIX = S + P where P is not just the long word percentage but also depends on the average number of words per sentence containing a long word (C). Average number of words (without taking into account the last word)  per sentence is 11.67 so with one more word added on the final result will be rounded down to 5, taking into account that only one long word can be the "maximum" longword word per word (due rounding reasons).
    So set P = (long word percentage * 0.45 + 0.87 * words with long word per sentence). So P equals to  (0.45 * 17.14) + (0.87*5) 
    P equals to 12.42 ( but it is needed it in percent so first and set numbers and keep the whole final result a  decimal but remember this  must have values bigger than one to go to the percentile)

P is converted in percentile set first value minus 100.
LIX equals to 11.67 + (12,42 -100)